## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the subjective nature of opinions on the healthcare system. The complexity of the U.S. healthcare system, with its mix of private and public elements, makes it challenging to categorize definitively as either market-based or command-based. Additionally, the perspectives gathered are primarily from online sources, which may not fully capture the nuances of policy and economic implications.

